<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/index.css" />
    <title>Inventory - <%= title %></title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <%- include('partials/nav') %> <%- include('partials/sidebar') %>
    <main
      class="bg-gradient-1 flex items-center content-center h-90-vh w-100 gap-2"
    >
      <div
        class="flex content-center gap-1 w-80 margin-0-auto md-gap-2 sm-flex-col sm-w-90"
      >
        <div class="flex flex-col items-start content-center gap-2 flex-1">
          <h1>Welcome to Inventory</h1>
          <p>Easily and securely manage your inventory</p>
          <a href="#about" class="btn-primary">Learn more</a>
        </div>
        <div
          class="flex flex-col items-start content-center gap-2 w-50 sm-w-100"
        >
          <img src="/assets/banner.svg" alt="" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </main>
    <section class="products-section sm-p-1">
      <div class="flex w-80 items-center content-between sm-w-90">
        <h2 id="products">Latest products</h2>
        <a href="/products" class="heading-link"
          >See all <img src="/assets/arrow.svg" alt="arrow"
        /></a>
      </div>
      <div
        class="grid grid-cols-4 w-80 gap-2 min-h-40 margin-0-auto md-w-90 sm-w-90"
      >
        <% if (products) { %> <% products.forEach(product => { %>
        <div class="grid-card">
          <div class="overlay"></div>
          <img src="<%= product.imageurl %> " alt="<%= product.title %> " />
          <a href="/products/<%= product.slug %> " class="product-title"
            ><%= product.title%></a
          >
        </div>
        <% }) %> <% } %>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="bg-gradient-2 category-section sm-p-1">
      <div class="flex w-80 items-center content-between sm-w-90">
        <h2 id="category">Latest categories</h2>
        <a href="/categories" class="heading-link"
          >See all
          <img src="/assets/arrow.svg" alt="arrow" />
        </a>
      </div>
      <div
        class="grid grid-cols-4 w-80 gap-2 min-h-40 margin-0-auto md-w-90 sm-w-90"
      >
        <% if (categories) { %> <% categories.forEach(category => { %>
        <div class="grid-card">
          <div class="overlay"></div>
          <img src="<%= category.imgurl %> " alt="<%= category.title %> " />
          <a href="/categories/<%- category.slug %>" class="category-title"
            ><%= category.title%></a
          >
        </div>
        <% }) %> <% } %>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section
      class="bg-gradient-1 about-section flex flex-col items-center content-center gap-2 padding-2 w-100 h-90-vh sm-p-1"
    >
      <div class="flex w-80 items-center content-between sm-w-90 sm-p-0-5">
        <h2 id="about">About inventory</h2>
      </div>
      <div
        class="flex content-center w-80 h-90-vh gap-2 items-center margin-0-auto lg-flex-col md-flex-col sm-w-90"
      >
        <div class="h-100 flex-1 w-50 md-w-80 lg-w-100 sm-w-100 sm-p-0-5">
          <img src="/assets/about.svg" alt="" />
        </div>
        <div
          class="flex flex-col items-start gap-1 h-100 flex-1 w-50 lg-w-100 md-w-100 sm-w-100 sm-p-0-5"
        >
          <h3>Project oveerview:</h3>
          <p class="line-h-2">
            This app was developed as part of The Odin Project curriculum, which
            emphasizes practical, project-based learning in web development. The
            aim was to gain hands-on experience by building a fully functional
            application, using modern tools and frameworks widely adopted in the
            industry.
          </p>
          <p class="line-h-2">
            One of the core objectives of the project was to work extensively
            with PostgreSQL, a relational database known for its reliability and
            flexibility. And to implement raw SQL queries to perform essential
            CRUD operations
          </p>
          <p class="line-h-2">
            Another significant aspect of the project was exploring user
            authentication and security best practices. By integrating bcrypt
            for password hashing and Passport.js for handling authentication, I
            learned how to secure user credentials and manage session-based
            authentication in a Node.js environment.
          </p>
          <a href="/about" class="btn-primary">Read more</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    <%- include('partials/footer') %>
    <script src="/navbar.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
